{
  "texts": [
    "At inference time, the final sample is typically obtained by evolving the initial noise, N (0, I) with ODE integration.",
    "This represents a deterministic sampler in which all the stochasticity is embedded in the initial noise sample (Gao et al., 2025).",
    "In contrast, the sampling process in DDPM is stochastic (Ho et al., 2020).",
    "Given that both diffusion models and flow matching can be seen generative modeling variants under arbitrary Markov processes (Holderrieth et al., 2025), we explore the use of a stochastic sampler within the physically based flow matching framework.",
    "The central idea is to evolve from time t to t = 1 and then return to t + dt using a different noise sample."
  ]
}